						<summary>

						<p>On a fifth slab found in Vishṇu temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1225, Uttarāyaṇa-Saṁkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Registers the grant of two perpetual lamps to the temple of Agastyēśvara at Niravadyapura by Kōmana-Peggaḍa and Rāmana-Peggaḍa, the sons of Gaṇanātha-Peggaḍa.</p>						

